Two adults died and two children sustained serious injuries after a collision on the N12 near Zuurbekom outside Carletonville on Tuesday.It is believed that the collision happened around 6:00 am as paramedics found two overturned vehicles on the scene.ER24 Spokesperson Werner Vermaak said the parents of an 18-month old and 9-year-old were found with fatal injuries near an overturned bakkie.He added: &#8220;All the occupants were ejected from the vehicle. The two children were found with serious injuries&#8221;.Both children were treated and stabilised on the scene before they were rushed through to a nearby hospital.The driver of the Polo sustained minor injuries and declined to be transported to hospital.The cause of the collision is not yet known.-TNA Reported